  <front>
   <head>ABSENCE AND DEATH. A PASTORAL.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">ev'ry eye that knew no cause to weep,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And peaceful minds were hush'd in pleasing sleep,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Two virgin nymphs, whom Love had left forlorn,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Ne'er clos'd their weeping eyes, from eve to morn:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">For Strephon's absence, Daphne's tears were shed,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And Hebe mourn'd her faithful Collin dead;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Their sorrows were not to each other known,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Alike they mourn'd, and silent was their moan;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Awhile they wept, 'till one the silence broke;</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thus Hebe answer'd, and thus Daphne spoke.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
